summary:
*MILD SPOILERS*
got a couple theories for 2x5! so we know they will be in the same place as The Ghost (though possibly not at...
body:
*MILD SPOILERS*

got a couple theories for 2x5! so we know they will be in the same place as The Ghost (though possibly not at the same time)

and we also know Villanelle sends Eve the flowers (funeral flowers, more specifically) most likely after Konstantin tells her she has to Kill Eve

we also know that Villanelle dresses up like she’s going to a funeral, and that she definitely visits Eve at some point with a knife

so I’ve been thinking this could go one of two ways: Villanelle is going to fake Eve’s death and is putting on a show for Konstantin to make him think she killed Eve and is over her, while also protecting Eve from further scrutiny from Konstantin/The Twelve. Villanelle does help Eve fake her death in the books, but we have been told the books diverged from the show, so who knows.

Another possibility could be that Villanelle is actually actively trying to get over Eve due to her believing Eve doesn’t care anymore, and is giving her a “funeral” to bury her feelings for her. We see V in the previews looking despondent and having a hotel worker pet her head, possibly because she’s still upset about Eve not showing up. I’m not certain she’ll stab Eve, but she might knick her with the poisoned knife.

The episode descriptions for 2x06 and 2x07 mention Villanelle immersing herself in the world of a new target and Eve having “worrying competition for Villanelle’s affections” respectively, which leads me to believe in my latter theory more. However, both Sandra and Jodie have talked about the possibility of a relationship and them trying to be together this season, so that confuses me.

These are just some of my ideas, and I’d love to hear what you guys think!

summary: I think about you all the time. I think about what you’re wearing, and what you’re doing, and who you’re doing it with. I think...
caption:
I think about you all the time. I think about what you’re wearing, and what you’re doing, and who you’re doing it with. I think about the friends you have, I think about what you eat before you go to work, and what shampoo you have, and what happened in your family. I think about your eyes and your mouth, and what you feel when you kill someone, I think about what you have for breakfast. I just want to know everything.

Killing Eve (2018-)

it was just going to be a small post about the control in the bill scene vs the lack of control js 2x04
summary: A huge thing for me about the club scene in 2x04 is it's the polar opposite of the scene where Villanelle kills Bill. When...
body:
A huge thing for me about the club scene in 2x04 is it’s the polar opposite of the scene where Villanelle kills Bill. When Villanelle goes into the club to kill Bill she is completely in control of the situation. She knows what Bill is going to do, she knows what she is going to do, she knows Eve will show up and find Bill. To her it was a game of chess where she’s let the other person have the offense because she knows exactly what they’ll do. The club scene in 2x04 is the exact opposite. In this game of chess she thought she had control and when it was slipping away from her she’s even tries to ‘help’ by giving a clue. Her sending the postcard to Eve was an attempt at control because she thought she knew what Eve would do afterwards. When Eve didn’t show up Villanelle realizes she doesn’t have any control over the situation anymore. To her it’s this realization of her not having control of Eve anymore because Eve doesn’t care about her or is as 'obsessed’ with her as Villanelle thought, at least that’s what Villanelle thinks because Eve doesn’t show up. I mean look back at the lipstick scene. Villanelle knows Eve is infatuated with her and will try on the lipstick, that’s why she puts the razor in there, it’s her way of showing Eve that Villanelle has control over her in a way. It’s like when you put a piece out in chess knowing the other person will take it but it will end up with them losing a more important piece. Eve not showing up at the Amsterdam crime scene isn’t even a matter, to Villanelle, of Eve not taking the bait in the game of chess. No it was Eve getting up and leaving the board to play a game of chess with someone else and leaving Villanelle without an ability to even take control of the situation. Villanelle can’t have control over the other player in her game if the other player quits playing. The club scene in 2x04 is more than just Villanelle losing control, it’s also her thinking that she won’t be able to take back control because Eve is done with their game.

    I mean to keep going on with the sense of a game of chess. It explains why the stabbing only made Villanelle even more intrigued with Eve. More obsessed. Think of a game of chess and you’re playing with someone who plays a certain style most of the game and so you assume their moves. When they make a move that you aren’t expecting it makes you lean forward in your seat. It draws your attention and makes you get more into the game because you realize that this person is thinking more intensely about this game than you thought. Villanelle thought she knew how Eve was playing their game and how she was seeing the board but the stabbing changed that in Villanelle’s eyes and made her realize Eve is even more into this thing between them than Villanelle ever imagined.
